Selenium Class 8

Sometimes test may not work on chrome so use other browsers like firefox

Implicit wait:
will be applied for findElement method

Explicit wait or WebDriver Wait:
is used to tell the webdriver to wait for a certain condition before throwing an exception for a specified condition

Explicit wait works with  ExpectedConditions class and waits until certain conditions are met or the given time is achieved

* sign in xpath is a wild card which can identify any tag name
//*[contains(text(), 'Welcome')]

Fluent Wait--->is a global wait
it is used to tell the webdriver to wait for a certain condition as well as its frequency beofre throing an exception

Implicit Wait-waits to locate the element
Explicit Wait-waits until a certain condition is met
Fluent Wait-sets timeouts, polling, and ignores needed exceptions

WebTables:
WebTables are elements on  the webpage, which are constructed by having rows and columns

Types od WebTables:
1)Static webtable
2)Dynamic webtable

Webtables consist of different sections or parts
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th><th> -- column data or
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>

